<h3>Lambent Quest Walkthrough</h3>
by Poodad Poopsticks
<table width="500" border="0"><tr><td>
<br>
Most of the lambent quest can be done at 30+ 
but are tough at that level. 35+ is a breeze solo 
for most of them. All the quests originate out of the Temple of Ro.

<h4>Lambent Boots</h4>
<b><i>Needed Items: Rune of one eye (Froon), 
Firewalker Boots, Lambent Stone </i></b>
<br><br>
Walthin Fireweaver in the Temple of Solosek Ro 
gives out this quest. Ask him about lambent 
boots and he will say: 
<br><br>
<b> Walthin Fireweaver says:</b> "Lambent Boots are 
the boots of choice for most Bards. If you can 
bring me Firewalker Boots from a Solusek Mage 
and the middle portion of the Rune of the One 
Eye from a Cyclops named Froon then I will 
give you a pair of Lambent Boots. Oh - I almost 
forgot - I will need a Lambent Sapphire as well." 
<br><br>
Solusek Magi are found in Solosek A. These 
goblins are lvl 28-31 and nuke hard. They can 
be found rather deep into Sol. Near king room 
usually but some wander from the jail area. 
<br><br>
Froon is in West Karana. He is always lvl 30 
and spawns near the ogre camp with another 
named cyclops named Choon (who is needed 
for lambent vambraces). He is pure melee and 
a long kite do to his huge amount of hp. 
<br><br>
You can get a lambent sapphire by getting a 
lambent stone (bought, or hill giants/griffons). 
Get two sapphires (can be bought in FP i think) 
and give the stone and sapphires too Garden in 
the temple of ro. When you hail him he won't 
talk about infusing lambent stones, but he will 
infuse lambent sapphires. Give him the two 
gems and the stone and you receive a lambent 
sapphire. Take the sapphire, rune, and boots 
to Walthin and you'll get a nice new pair of 
lambent boots.<br><br>
Ac: 11, Cha: 1, SV All: 2. 
<br><br>
<h4>Lambent Greaves</h4>
<b><i>Items needed: Shin greaves, Icey Greaves, 
Lambent Stone </i></b>
<br><br>
This is also given out by Walthin Fireweaver. 
Hail him and ask him about lambent greaves:
<br><br> 
<b>Walthin Fireweaver says:</b> "There are no finer 
leggings for a Bard then Lambent Greaves. 
Collect for me two lesser pair of greaves and I 
will give you some. Bring me Icy Greaves from 
an Elite Goblin Guard in the Caverns of 
Permafrost and Shin Greaves from a Shin Ghoul 
Knight, as well as a Lambent Fire Opal and I will 
gift you a pair of Lambent Greaves."
<br><br>
The elite goblin guard's spawn deep in 
permafrost near the king room. They are about 
24-30 but spawn near a bunch of other gobbies 
that are always aggro (ouch). Also the elites 
themselves can see-invis. They drop the 
greaves about 1 in 10 trys. 
<br><br>
Though Walthin say he needs Shin greaves for 
a Shin Ghoul Knight, any frog with the word Shin 
in their name will drop the greaves (and 
gauntlets). They're lvl's can range from the 
warriors being 25ish to the knights who are 28- 
31. They can be found all over uguk and lguk 
just wander a bit. 
<br><br>
Lambent Fire opal requires one lambent stone 
and two fire opals. The two fire opals can be 
bought from Genni in the temple of ro for 550 
gold coins each (1100 gold total). Then give 
the stone and two opals to Ostorm in the 
temple of ro and he will infuse them, though he 
won't talk about it either if you hail him. Take 
all three items back to walthin and you get a 
new pair of lambent greaves.
<br><br>
AC: 12, Cha: 1, Agi: 5. 
<br><br>
<h4>Lambent Breastplate</h4> 
(I haven't done this quest myself 
so this info is sketchy). 
<br><br>
Go to the temple of Ro and hail Cryssia 
Stardreamer and ask her about a Lambent 
Breastplate: 
<br><br>
<b>Cryssia Stardreamer says:</b> "Lambent 
Breastplates are not cheap, but I can get you 
one if you bring me a few items that I need for 
later trades with the followers of Solusek Ro. 
Bring me a Basalt Carapace from a Basalt 
Gargoyle in the Caverns of Guk and a Gypsy 
Lute from the Castle of Mistmoore. You will also 
need to see Genni about getting me a Lambent 
Ruby. Collect these items for me, and I will give 
you a Lambent Breastplate." 
<br><br>
The Basalt Gargoyle is in LGuk and is about 30- 
34. I've seen two near the assasin spawn and 
they are static, always spawn at that point and 
don't wander. I've never actually tried to kill 
these guys so i can't put much else on them :(. 
<br><br>
The Gypsy Lute drops in Mistmoore off of Gypsy 
Musicians. They are about lvl 30 and spawn in 
a room with three other gypsys (not sure if 
they all drop the lute) and a named gypsy. 
Mistmoore is a mean zone so this item is rather 
difficult to obtain. Also don't get the gypsy lute 
confused with the Lute of the Gypsy 
Princesses. Two different Lutes. 
<br><br>For the lambent ruby get two rubies and a lambent 
stone and take them to Vilissia in the Temple of 
Ro and she will infuse them. Take all three 
items to Cryssia and she'll give you a lambent 
Breastplate.
<br><br>
AC: 20, Sta: 5, HP: 25, Cha: 1 
<br><br>

<h4>Lambent Vambraces</h4>
<b><i>Items Needed: Rune of one eye (Choon), Fiery 
Vambraces, Lambent Stone </i></b>
Cryssia also gives out the quest for lambent 
vambaces. Hail her and ask "what lambent 
vambraces" and she'll say: 
<br><br>
<b>Cryssia Stardreamer says:</b> "I will give you 
Lambent Vambraces if you can acquire the 
following items for me - Fiery Vambraces from 
a Solusek Champion and the top portion of the 
Rune of the One Eye from a Cyclops named 
Choon. You will also need to see Genni about 
getting me a Lambent Sapphire. Acquire these 
items for me and I will give you Lambent 
Vambraces."
<br><br>
Solusek Champions spawn in Sol A and are 
pretty common. They are also lvl 28-31 
(noticing a trend?). They have multiple spawn 
points, one near the king room, another at the 
river of fire. Not too difficult of a gobbie but 
likes to run. 
<br><br>
Choon spawns with Froon in West Karana and is 
lvl 30. Spawns near the ogre camp and is a 
long kite because of his large amount of hp. 
<br><br>
Next get a lambent stone and two sapphires 
and give them to Gardern in the temple of Ro. 
After he infuses them give the items to Cryssia 
and you'll have your new Lambent Vambraces.
<br><br>
Ac: 11, Cha: 1, SV All: 2 
<br><br>

<h4>Lambent Bracers </h4>
<b><i>Items needed: Griffene Charm, Dark bone 
bracelet, lambent stone. </i></b>
Hail Cryssia again and ask her "What lambent 
bracers?" She'll reply: 
<br><br>
<b>Cryssia Stardreamer says:</b> "Lambent Bracers 
are nice armor, and do not have the same level 
of complexity that other Lambent Armor 
possesses. If you can fetch for me a Dark 
Boned Bracelet from a Greater Dark Boned 
Skeleton, a Griffenne Charm from a Griffenne 
and a Lambent Fire Opal then I will give you a 
Lambent Bracer." 
<br><br>
Easiest of the lambent quests in my opinion. 
<br><br>
The Greater Dark Boned spawns in Unrest in the 
basement. He's lvl 26-30 and is undead (go 
figure). I've heard the drop rate of the bracelet 
is very rare, but i got one in one hour of 
camping the basement for exp. 
<br><br>
Griffenne's spawn in North Karana and are 
about lvl 25-28 but fight much higher than their 
lvl. They wander the zone so you might want a 
tracker to hunt them down. They are also 
pretty fast. Took me 12 kills or 
so, so a semi-uncommon drop. Griffons also drop the charm but 
they are much higher lvl. 
<br><br>
For the lambent fire opal go back to the temple 
of ro. Give Genni 550 gold pieces for each opal 
(1110 total). Give the stone and the two gems 
to Ostorm in the Temple of Ro and he'll infuse 
them. Take these all back to Cyrissia and you'll 
get a lambent bracer.
<br><br>
Ac: 9, Str: 4, Cha: 1 
<br><br>

<h4>Lambent Gauntlets</h4>
<b><i>Items needed: Black Silk Gloves, Shin 
Gauntlets, Lambent Stone.</i></b>
<br><br>
In the temple of Ro hail Walthin again and ask 
him "what lambent gauntlets?" 
<br><br>
<b>Walthin Fireweaver says:</b> "Lambent Gauntlets 
are exceptionally well made gauntlets. If you 
are interested, I will give you a pair - but you 
will have to bring me the following items that I 
need for a trade with the followers of Solusek 
Ro. I need Shin Gauntlets from a Froglok Shin 
Knight and Black Silk Gloves from a Deathly 
Usher in Castle Mistmoore. You will also need 
to talk to Genni about getting me a Lambent 
Star Ruby. Bring me these items and you will 
earn Lambent Gauntlets."
<br><br> 
This is one of the easier quests to do. The 
gloves drop in Mistmoore, jail or graveyard. 
You can get these at lvl 26 or so. Just group in 
the graveyard for exp. It drops off more than 
one mob but the only one i can remember is 
the Deathly Users, lvl 30ish melee class. 
Uncommon spawn but none too rare. Usher 
spawns in castle/jail. I'm pretty sure a mob in 
the graveyard drops the gloves too but the 
name eludes me at the moment. They drop the 
gloves pretty rarely so this might take some 
camp time, they also drop the rune of ivy for 
the Ivy Etched Helm quest, so if it drops and if 
any rangers are nearby, be a sweety and let 
them loot it. 
<br><br>
The Shin gauntlets were a bit harder since i 
play on Tallon Zek and it's a dark controlled 
dungeon. The Shin Gauntlets drop in upper or lower guk 
off of any of the shin frogs. Kill 
any mob with the prefix shin in their name. Levels can range from 
25-31. Live or undead, both drop gauntlets. Drop is 
uncommon but mobs are everywhere. About 5- 
10 frogs and you should have the gloves.
<br><br>
Lambent Star rubies can be made by Genni in 
the temple of Ro. Give her two star rubies and 
a lambent stone and she'll give you a lambent 
star ruby. Turn these three items into Walthen 
and you'll get a pair of Lambent Gauntlets. 
<br><br>
Ac: 12, Cha: 1, Dex: 5 
<br><br>

<h4>Lambent Helm</h4> 
(again haven't done this quest so 
info will be sketchy) 
<br><br>
Cyrissia gives out the quest for the helm in the 
temple of Ro. Hail her and ask "what lambent 
helm?" and she'll say: 
<br><br>
<b>Cryssia Stardreamer says:</b> "I can give you a 
Lambent Helm, but you will need to fetch me a 
few items that I need for later trades with the 
followers of Solusek Ro. I require an Opoline 
Helm from a Deepwater Goblin and a Mudwater 
Rune from a Lizard Fanatic of Cazic Thule. 
Finally, you will also need to see Genni about 
getting me a Lambent Star Ruby. Bring me 
these items, and I will give to you a Lambent 
Helm."
<br><br>
Deepwater Goblins are in the Oasis of Marr 
underwater in the lake. They can be warriors, 
wizards, or shamans and fight rather nasty. Lvl 
can range from 33-37 and helm drops rarely. 
About one in 10 kills. 
<br><br>
Lizard Fanatics spawn in the Lost temple of 
Cazic-Thule. They are lvl 30-32 and drop the 
rune quite often from what I hear (never tried 
this). Spawns in to the courtyard. 
<br><br>
For the lambent star ruby get two star rubies 
and a lambent stone and give them to Genni int 
he temple of ro. After you get the stone back 
give the stone, rune, and helm to Cyrissia and 
you'll get a lambent helm. 
<br><br>
Ac: 13, Int: 5, Cha: 3 
<br><br><br>
